29 std::string getCudaVersionString() {
30  int driver_version = 0;
31  cuDriverGetVersion(&driver_version);
32  // The version is returned as (1000 major + 10 minor).
33  std::stringstream stream;
34  stream << "CUDA " << driver_version / 1000 << "."
35  << driver_version % 1000 / 10;
36  return stream.str();

39 pi_result map_error(CUresult result) {
40  switch (result) {
41  case CUDA_SUCCESS:
42  return PI_SUCCESS;
43  case CUDA_ERROR_NOT_PERMITTED:
44  return PI_INVALID_OPERATION;
45  case CUDA_ERROR_INVALID_CONTEXT:
46  return PI_INVALID_CONTEXT;
47  case CUDA_ERROR_INVALID_DEVICE:
48  return PI_INVALID_DEVICE;
49  case CUDA_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE:
50  return PI_INVALID_VALUE;
51  case CUDA_ERROR_OUT_OF_MEMORY:
52  return PI_OUT_OF_HOST_MEMORY;
53  case CUDA_ERROR_LAUNCH_OUT_OF_RESOURCES:
54  return PI_OUT_OF_RESOURCES;
55  default:
56  return PI_ERROR_UNKNOWN;
57  }
58 }

60 // Iterates over the event wait list, returns correct pi_result error codes.
61 // Invokes the callback for the latest event of each queue in the wait list.
62 // The callback must take a single pi_event argument and return a pi_result.
63 template <typename Func>
64 pi_result forLatestEvents(const pi_event *event_wait_list,
65  std::size_t num_events_in_wait_list, Func &&f) {
66 
67  if (event_wait_list == nullptr || num_events_in_wait_list == 0) {
68  return PI_INVALID_EVENT_WAIT_LIST;
69  }
70 
71  // Fast path if we only have a single event
72  if (num_events_in_wait_list == 1) {
73  return f(event_wait_list[0]);
74  }
75 
76  std::vector<pi_event> events{event_wait_list,
77  event_wait_list + num_events_in_wait_list};
78  std::sort(events.begin(), events.end(), [](pi_event e0, pi_event e1) {
79  // Tiered sort creating sublists of streams (smallest value first) in which
80  // the corresponding events are sorted into a sequence of newest first.
81  return e0->get_queue()->stream_ < e1->get_queue()->stream_ ||
82  (e0->get_queue()->stream_ == e1->get_queue()->stream_ &&
83  e0->get_event_id() > e1->get_event_id());
84  });
85 
86  bool first = true;
87  CUstream lastSeenStream = 0;
88  for (pi_event event : events) {
89  if (!event || (!first && event->get_queue()->stream_ == lastSeenStream)) {
90  continue;
91  }
92 
93  first = false;
94  lastSeenStream = event->get_queue()->stream_;
95 
96  auto result = f(event);
97  if (result != PI_SUCCESS) {
98  return result;
99  }
100  }
101 
102  return PI_SUCCESS;
103 }

112 pi_result check_error(CUresult result, const char *function, int line,
113  const char *file) {
114  if (result == CUDA_SUCCESS || result == CUDA_ERROR_DEINITIALIZED) {
115  return PI_SUCCESS;
116  }
117 
118  const char *errorString = nullptr;
119  const char *errorName = nullptr;
120  cuGetErrorName(result, &errorName);
121  cuGetErrorString(result, &errorString);
122  std::cerr << "\nPI CUDA ERROR:"
123  << "\n\tValue: " << result
124  << "\n\tName: " << errorName
125  << "\n\tDescription: " << errorString
126  << "\n\tFunction: " << function
127  << "\n\tSource Location: " << file << ":" << line << "\n"
128  << std::endl;
129 
130  if (std::getenv("PI_CUDA_ABORT") != nullptr) {
131  std::abort();
132  }
133 
134  throw map_error(result);
135 }

162 class ScopedContext {
163 public:
164  ScopedContext(pi_context ctxt) {
165  if (!ctxt) {
166  throw PI_INVALID_CONTEXT;
167  }
168 
169  CUcontext desired = ctxt->get();
170  CUcontext original = nullptr;
171 
172  PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuCtxGetCurrent(&original));
173 
174  // Make sure the desired context is active on the current thread, setting
175  // it if necessary
176  if (original != desired) {
177  PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuCtxSetCurrent(desired));
178  }
179  }
180 
181  ~ScopedContext() {}
182 };

185 template <typename T, typename Assign>
186 pi_result getInfoImpl(size_t param_value_size, void *param_value,
187  size_t *param_value_size_ret, T value, size_t value_size,
188  Assign &&assign_func) {
189 
190  if (param_value != nullptr) {
191 
192  if (param_value_size < value_size) {
193  return PI_INVALID_VALUE;
194  }
195 
196  assign_func(param_value, value, value_size);
197  }
198 
199  if (param_value_size_ret != nullptr) {
200  *param_value_size_ret = value_size;
201  }
202 
203  return PI_SUCCESS;
204 }

206 template <typename T>
207 pi_result getInfo(size_t param_value_size, void *param_value,
208  size_t *param_value_size_ret, T value) {
209 
210  auto assignment = [](void *param_value, T value, size_t value_size) {
211  // Ignore unused parameter
212  (void)value_size;
213 
214  *static_cast<T *>(param_value) = value;
215  };
216 
217  return getInfoImpl(param_value_size, param_value, param_value_size_ret, value,
218  sizeof(T), assignment);
219 }
220 
221 template <typename T>
222 pi_result getInfoArray(size_t array_length, size_t param_value_size,
223  void *param_value, size_t *param_value_size_ret,
224  T *value) {
225  return getInfoImpl(param_value_size, param_value, param_value_size_ret, value,
226  array_length * sizeof(T), memcpy);
227 }

245 // Determine local work sizes that result in uniform work groups.
246 // The default threadsPerBlock only require handling the first work_dim
247 // dimension.
248 void guessLocalWorkSize(size_t *threadsPerBlock, const size_t *global_work_size,
249  const size_t maxThreadsPerBlock[3], pi_kernel kernel,
250  pi_uint32 local_size) {
251  assert(threadsPerBlock != nullptr);
252  assert(global_work_size != nullptr);
253  assert(kernel != nullptr);
254  int recommendedBlockSize, minGrid;
255 
256  PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuOccupancyMaxPotentialBlockSize(
257  &minGrid, &recommendedBlockSize, kernel->get(), NULL, local_size,
258  maxThreadsPerBlock[0]));
259 
260  (void)minGrid; // Not used, avoid warnings
261 
262  threadsPerBlock[0] = std::min(
263  maxThreadsPerBlock[0],
264  std::min(global_work_size[0], static_cast<size_t>(recommendedBlockSize)));
265 
266  // Find a local work group size that is a divisor of the global
267  // work group size to produce uniform work groups.
268  while (0u != (global_work_size[0] % threadsPerBlock[0])) {
269  --threadsPerBlock[0];
270  }
271 }

326 _pi_event::_pi_event(pi_command_type type, pi_context context, pi_queue queue)
327  : commandType_{type}, refCount_{1}, hasBeenWaitedOn_{false},
328  isRecorded_{false}, isStarted_{false}, evEnd_{nullptr}, evStart_{nullptr},
329  evQueued_{nullptr}, queue_{queue}, context_{context} {
330 
331  bool profilingEnabled = queue_->properties_ & PI_QUEUE_PROFILING_ENABLE;
332 
333  PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuEventCreate(
334  &evEnd_, profilingEnabled ? CU_EVENT_DEFAULT : CU_EVENT_DISABLE_TIMING));
335 
336  if (profilingEnabled) {
337  PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuEventCreate(&evQueued_, CU_EVENT_DEFAULT));
338  PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuEventCreate(&evStart_, CU_EVENT_DEFAULT));
339  }
340 
341  if (queue_ != nullptr) {
342  cuda_piQueueRetain(queue_);
343  }
344  cuda_piContextRetain(context_);

354 pi_result _pi_event::start() {
355  assert(!is_started());
356  pi_result result = PI_SUCCESS;
357 
358  try {
359  if (queue_->properties_ & PI_QUEUE_PROFILING_ENABLE) {
360  // NOTE: This relies on the default stream to be unused.
361  result = PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuEventRecord(evQueued_, 0));
362  result = PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuEventRecord(evStart_, queue_->get()));
363  }
364  } catch (pi_result error) {
365  result = error;
366  }
367 
368  isStarted_ = true;
369  return result;
370 }
371 
372 bool _pi_event::is_completed() const noexcept {
373  if (!isRecorded_) {
374  return false;
375  }
376  if (!hasBeenWaitedOn_) {
377  const CUresult ret = cuEventQuery(evEnd_);
378  if (ret != CUDA_SUCCESS && ret != CUDA_ERROR_NOT_READY) {
379  PI_CHECK_ERROR(ret);
380  return false;
381  }
382  if (ret == CUDA_ERROR_NOT_READY) {
383  return false;
384  }
385  }
386  return true;
387 }

414 pi_result _pi_event::record() {
415 
416  if (is_recorded() || !is_started()) {
417  return PI_INVALID_EVENT;
418  }
419 
420  pi_result result = PI_INVALID_OPERATION;
421 
422  if (!queue_) {
423  return PI_INVALID_QUEUE;
424  }
425 
426  CUstream cuStream = queue_->get();
427 
428  try {
429  eventId_ = queue_->get_next_event_id();
430  if (eventId_ == 0) {
431  cl::sycl::detail::pi::die(
432  "Unrecoverable program state reached in event identifier overflow");
433  }
434  result = PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuEventRecord(evEnd_, cuStream));
435  } catch (pi_result error) {
436  result = error;
437  }
438 
439  if (result == PI_SUCCESS) {
440  isRecorded_ = true;
441  }
442 
443  return result;
444 }
445 
446 pi_result _pi_event::wait() {
447  pi_result retErr;
448  try {
449  retErr = PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuEventSynchronize(evEnd_));
450  hasBeenWaitedOn_ = true;
451  } catch (pi_result error) {
452  retErr = error;
453  }
454 
455  return retErr;
456 }
457 
458 pi_result _pi_event::release() {
459  assert(queue_ != nullptr);
460  PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuEventDestroy(evEnd_));
461 
462  if (queue_->properties_ & PI_QUEUE_PROFILING_ENABLE) {
463  PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuEventDestroy(evQueued_));
464  PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuEventDestroy(evStart_));
465  }
466 
467  return PI_SUCCESS;
468 }

470 // makes all future work submitted to queue wait for all work captured in event.
471 pi_result enqueueEventWait(pi_queue queue, pi_event event) {
472  // for native events, the cuStreamWaitEvent call is used.
473  // This makes all future work submitted to stream wait for all
474  // work captured in event.
475  if (queue->get() != event->get_queue()->get()) {
476  return PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuStreamWaitEvent(queue->get(), event->get(), 0));
477  }
478  return PI_SUCCESS;

489 bool get_kernel_metadata(std::string metadataName, const char *tag,
490  std::string &kernelName) {
491  const size_t tagLength = strlen(tag);
492  const size_t metadataNameLength = metadataName.length();
493  if (metadataNameLength >= tagLength &&
494  metadataName.compare(metadataNameLength - tagLength, tagLength, tag) ==
495  0) {
496  kernelName = metadataName.substr(0, metadataNameLength - tagLength);
497  return true;
498  }
499  return false;
500 }

502 pi_result _pi_program::set_metadata(const pi_device_binary_property *metadata,
503  size_t length) {
504  for (size_t i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
505  const pi_device_binary_property metadataElement = metadata[i];
506  std::string metadataElementName{metadataElement->Name};
507  std::string kernelName;
508 
509  // If metadata is reqd_work_group_size record it for the corresponding
510  // kernel name.
511  if (get_kernel_metadata(metadataElementName,
512  __SYCL_PI_PROGRAM_METADATA_TAG_REQD_WORK_GROUP_SIZE,
513  kernelName)) {
514  assert(metadataElement->ValSize ==
515  sizeof(std::uint64_t) + sizeof(std::uint32_t) * 3 &&
516  "Unexpected size for reqd_work_group_size metadata");
517 
518  // Get pointer to data, skipping 64-bit size at the start of the data.
519  const auto *reqdWorkGroupElements =
520  reinterpret_cast<const std::uint32_t *>(metadataElement->ValAddr) + 2;
521  kernelReqdWorkGroupSizeMD_[kernelName] =
522  std::make_tuple(reqdWorkGroupElements[0], reqdWorkGroupElements[1],
523  reqdWorkGroupElements[2]);
524  }
525  }
526  return PI_SUCCESS;
527 }

537 pi_result _pi_program::build_program(const char *build_options) {
538 
539  this->buildOptions_ = build_options;
540 
541  constexpr const unsigned int numberOfOptions = 4u;
542 
543  CUjit_option options[numberOfOptions];
544  void *optionVals[numberOfOptions];
545 
546  // Pass a buffer for info messages
547  options[0] = CU_JIT_INFO_LOG_BUFFER;
548  optionVals[0] = (void *)infoLog_;
549  // Pass the size of the info buffer
550  options[1] = CU_JIT_INFO_LOG_BUFFER_SIZE_BYTES;
551  optionVals[1] = (void *)(long)MAX_LOG_SIZE;
552  // Pass a buffer for error message
553  options[2] = CU_JIT_ERROR_LOG_BUFFER;
554  optionVals[2] = (void *)errorLog_;
555  // Pass the size of the error buffer
556  options[3] = CU_JIT_ERROR_LOG_BUFFER_SIZE_BYTES;
557  optionVals[3] = (void *)(long)MAX_LOG_SIZE;
558 
559  auto result = PI_CHECK_ERROR(
560  cuModuleLoadDataEx(&module_, static_cast<const void *>(binary_),
561  numberOfOptions, options, optionVals));
562 
563  const auto success = (result == PI_SUCCESS);
564 
565  buildStatus_ =
566  success ? PI_PROGRAM_BUILD_STATUS_SUCCESS : PI_PROGRAM_BUILD_STATUS_ERROR;
567 
568  // If no exception, result is correct
569  return success ? PI_SUCCESS : PI_BUILD_PROGRAM_FAILURE;
570 }

588 template <typename T> class ReleaseGuard {
589 private:
590  T Captive;
591 
592  static pi_result callRelease(pi_device Captive) {
593  return cuda_piDeviceRelease(Captive);
594  }
595 
596  static pi_result callRelease(pi_context Captive) {
597  return cuda_piContextRelease(Captive);
598  }
599 
600  static pi_result callRelease(pi_mem Captive) {
601  return cuda_piMemRelease(Captive);
602  }
603 
604  static pi_result callRelease(pi_program Captive) {
605  return cuda_piProgramRelease(Captive);
606  }
607 
608  static pi_result callRelease(pi_kernel Captive) {
609  return cuda_piKernelRelease(Captive);
610  }
611 
612  static pi_result callRelease(pi_queue Captive) {
613  return cuda_piQueueRelease(Captive);
614  }
615 
616  static pi_result callRelease(pi_event Captive) {
617  return cuda_piEventRelease(Captive);
618  }
619 
620 public:
621  ReleaseGuard() = delete;
623  explicit ReleaseGuard(T Obj) : Captive(Obj) {}
624  ReleaseGuard(ReleaseGuard &&Other) noexcept : Captive(Other.Captive) {
625  Other.Captive = nullptr;
626  }
627 
628  ReleaseGuard(const ReleaseGuard &) = delete;
629 
632  ~ReleaseGuard() {
633  if (Captive != nullptr) {
634  pi_result ret = callRelease(Captive);
635  if (ret != PI_SUCCESS) {
636  // A reported CUDA error is either an implementation or an asynchronous
637  // CUDA error for which it is unclear if the function that reported it
638  // succeeded or not. Either way, the state of the program is compromised
639  // and likely unrecoverable.
640  cl::sycl::detail::pi::die(
641  "Unrecoverable program state reached in cuda_piMemRelease");
642  }
643  }
644  }
645 
646  ReleaseGuard &operator=(const ReleaseGuard &) = delete;
647 
648  ReleaseGuard &operator=(ReleaseGuard &&Other) {
649  Captive = Other.Captive;
650  Other.Captive = nullptr;
651  return *this;
652  }
653 
656  void dismiss() { Captive = nullptr; }
657 };

674 pi_result cuda_piPlatformsGet(pi_uint32 num_entries, pi_platform *platforms,
675  pi_uint32 *num_platforms) {
676 
677  try {
678  static std::once_flag initFlag;
679  static pi_uint32 numPlatforms = 1;
680  static std::vector<_pi_platform> platformIds;
681 
682  if (num_entries == 0 && platforms != nullptr) {
683  return PI_INVALID_VALUE;
684  }
685  if (platforms == nullptr && num_platforms == nullptr) {
686  return PI_INVALID_VALUE;
687  }
688 
689  pi_result err = PI_SUCCESS;
690 
691  std::call_once(
692  initFlag,
693  [](pi_result &err) {
694  if (cuInit(0) != CUDA_SUCCESS) {
695  numPlatforms = 0;
696  return;
697  }
698  int numDevices = 0;
699  err = PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuDeviceGetCount(&numDevices));
700  if (numDevices == 0) {
701  numPlatforms = 0;
702  return;
703  }
704  try {
705  // make one platform per device
706  numPlatforms = numDevices;
707  platformIds.resize(numDevices);
708 
709  for (int i = 0; i < numDevices; ++i) {
710  CUdevice device;
711  err = PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuDeviceGet(&device, i));
712  platformIds[i].devices_.emplace_back(
713  new _pi_device{device, &platformIds[i]});
714 
715  {
716  const auto &dev = platformIds[i].devices_.back().get();
717  size_t maxWorkGroupSize = 0u;
718  size_t maxThreadsPerBlock[3] = {};
719  pi_result retError = cuda_piDeviceGetInfo(
720  dev, PI_DEVICE_INFO_MAX_WORK_ITEM_SIZES,
721  sizeof(maxThreadsPerBlock), maxThreadsPerBlock, nullptr);
722  assert(retError == PI_SUCCESS);
723  (void)retError;
724 
725  retError = cuda_piDeviceGetInfo(
726  dev, PI_DEVICE_INFO_MAX_WORK_GROUP_SIZE,
727  sizeof(maxWorkGroupSize), &maxWorkGroupSize, nullptr);
728  assert(retError == PI_SUCCESS);
729 
730  dev->save_max_work_item_sizes(sizeof(maxThreadsPerBlock),
731  maxThreadsPerBlock);
732  dev->save_max_work_group_size(maxWorkGroupSize);
733  }
734  }
735  } catch (const std::bad_alloc &) {
736  // Signal out-of-memory situation
737  for (int i = 0; i < numDevices; ++i) {
738  platformIds[i].devices_.clear();
739  }
740  platformIds.clear();
741  err = PI_OUT_OF_HOST_MEMORY;
742  } catch (...) {
743  // Clear and rethrow to allow retry
744  for (int i = 0; i < numDevices; ++i) {
745  platformIds[i].devices_.clear();
746  }
747  platformIds.clear();
748  throw;
749  }
750  },
751  err);
752 
753  if (num_platforms != nullptr) {
754  *num_platforms = numPlatforms;
755  }
756 
757  if (platforms != nullptr) {
758  for (unsigned i = 0; i < std::min(num_entries, numPlatforms); ++i) {
759  platforms[i] = &platformIds[i];
760  }
761  }
762 
763  return err;
764  } catch (pi_result err) {
765  return err;
766  } catch (...) {
767  return PI_OUT_OF_RESOURCES;
768  }
769 }

807 pi_result cuda_piDevicesGet(pi_platform platform, pi_device_type device_type,
808  pi_uint32 num_entries, pi_device *devices,
809  pi_uint32 *num_devices) {
810 
811  pi_result err = PI_SUCCESS;
812  const bool askingForDefault = device_type == PI_DEVICE_TYPE_DEFAULT;
813  const bool askingForGPU = device_type & PI_DEVICE_TYPE_GPU;
814  const bool returnDevices = askingForDefault || askingForGPU;
815 
816  size_t numDevices = returnDevices ? platform->devices_.size() : 0;
817 
818  try {
819  if (num_devices) {
820  *num_devices = numDevices;
821  }
822 
823  if (returnDevices && devices) {
824  for (size_t i = 0; i < std::min(size_t(num_entries), numDevices); ++i) {
825  devices[i] = platform->devices_[i].get();
826  }
827  }
828 
829  return err;
830  } catch (pi_result err) {
831  return err;
832  } catch (...) {
833  return PI_OUT_OF_RESOURCES;
834  }
835 }

913 pi_result cuda_piextDeviceSelectBinary(pi_device device,
914  pi_device_binary *binaries,
915  pi_uint32 num_binaries,
916  pi_uint32 *selected_binary) {
917  // Ignore unused parameter
918  (void)device;
919 
920  if (!binaries) {
921  cl::sycl::detail::pi::die("No list of device images provided");
922  }
923  if (num_binaries < 1) {
924  cl::sycl::detail::pi::die("No binary images in the list");
925  }
926 
927  // Look for an image for the NVPTX64 target, and return the first one that is
928  // found
929  for (pi_uint32 i = 0; i < num_binaries; i++) {
930  if (strcmp(binaries[i]->DeviceTargetSpec,
931  __SYCL_PI_DEVICE_BINARY_TARGET_NVPTX64) == 0) {
932  *selected_binary = i;
933  return PI_SUCCESS;
934  }
935  }
936 
937  // No image can be loaded for the given device
938  return PI_INVALID_BINARY;
939 }

941 pi_result cuda_piextGetDeviceFunctionPointer(pi_device device,
942  pi_program program,
943  const char *func_name,
944  pi_uint64 *func_pointer_ret) {
945  // Check if device passed is the same the device bound to the context
946  assert(device == program->get_context()->get_device());
947  assert(func_pointer_ret != nullptr);
948 
949  CUfunction func;
950  CUresult ret = cuModuleGetFunction(&func, program->get(), func_name);
951  *func_pointer_ret = reinterpret_cast<pi_uint64>(func);
952  pi_result retError = PI_SUCCESS;
953 
954  if (ret != CUDA_SUCCESS && ret != CUDA_ERROR_NOT_FOUND)
955  retError = PI_CHECK_ERROR(ret);
956  if (ret == CUDA_ERROR_NOT_FOUND) {
957  *func_pointer_ret = 0;
958  retError = PI_INVALID_KERNEL_NAME;
959  }
960 
961  return retError;
962 }

1015  cl::sycl::detail::pi::assertion(max_z >= 0);

1620  case PI_DEVICE_INFO_USM_HOST_SUPPORT: {
1621  // from cl_intel_unified_shared_memory: "The host memory access capabilities
1622  // apply to any host allocation."
1623  //
1624  // query if/how the device can access page-locked host memory, possibly
1625  // through PCIe, using the same pointer as the host
1626  pi_bitfield value = {};
1627  if (getAttribute(device, CU_DEVICE_ATTRIBUTE_UNIFIED_ADDRESSING)) {
1628  // the device shares a unified address space with the host
1629  if (getAttribute(device, CU_DEVICE_ATTRIBUTE_COMPUTE_CAPABILITY_MAJOR) >=
1630  6) {
1631  // compute capability 6.x introduces operations that are atomic with
1632  // respect to other CPUs and GPUs in the system
1633  value = PI_USM_ACCESS | PI_USM_ATOMIC_ACCESS |
1634  PI_USM_CONCURRENT_ACCESS | PI_USM_CONCURRENT_ATOMIC_ACCESS;
1635  } else {
1636  // on GPU architectures with compute capability lower than 6.x, atomic
1637  // operations from the GPU to CPU memory will not be atomic with respect
1638  // to CPU initiated atomic operations
1639  value = PI_USM_ACCESS | PI_USM_CONCURRENT_ACCESS;
1640  }
1641  }
1642  return getInfo(param_value_size, param_value, param_value_size_ret, value);
1643  }
1644  case PI_DEVICE_INFO_USM_DEVICE_SUPPORT: {
1645  // from cl_intel_unified_shared_memory:
1646  // "The device memory access capabilities apply to any device allocation
1647  // associated with this device."
1648  //
1649  // query how the device can access memory allocated on the device itself (?)
1650  pi_bitfield value = PI_USM_ACCESS | PI_USM_ATOMIC_ACCESS |
1651  PI_USM_CONCURRENT_ACCESS |
1652  PI_USM_CONCURRENT_ATOMIC_ACCESS;
1653  return getInfo(param_value_size, param_value, param_value_size_ret, value);
1654  }
1655  case PI_DEVICE_INFO_USM_SINGLE_SHARED_SUPPORT: {
1656  // from cl_intel_unified_shared_memory:
1657  // "The single device shared memory access capabilities apply to any shared
1658  // allocation associated with this device."
1659  //
1660  // query if/how the device can access managed memory associated to it
1661  pi_bitfield value = {};
1662  if (getAttribute(device, CU_DEVICE_ATTRIBUTE_MANAGED_MEMORY)) {
1663  // the device can allocate managed memory on this system
1664  value = PI_USM_ACCESS | PI_USM_ATOMIC_ACCESS;
1665  }
1666  if (getAttribute(device, CU_DEVICE_ATTRIBUTE_CONCURRENT_MANAGED_ACCESS)) {
1667  // the device can coherently access managed memory concurrently with the
1668  // CPU
1669  value |= PI_USM_CONCURRENT_ACCESS;
1670  if (getAttribute(device, CU_DEVICE_ATTRIBUTE_COMPUTE_CAPABILITY_MAJOR) >=
1671  6) {
1672  // compute capability 6.x introduces operations that are atomic with
1673  // respect to other CPUs and GPUs in the system
1674  value |= PI_USM_CONCURRENT_ATOMIC_ACCESS;
1675  }
1676  }
1677  return getInfo(param_value_size, param_value, param_value_size_ret, value);
1678  }
1679  case PI_DEVICE_INFO_USM_CROSS_SHARED_SUPPORT: {
1680  // from cl_intel_unified_shared_memory:
1681  // "The cross-device shared memory access capabilities apply to any shared
1682  // allocation associated with this device, or to any shared memory
1683  // allocation on another device that also supports the same cross-device
1684  // shared memory access capability."
1685  //
1686  // query if/how the device can access managed memory associated to other
1687  // devices
1688  pi_bitfield value = {};
1689  if (getAttribute(device, CU_DEVICE_ATTRIBUTE_MANAGED_MEMORY)) {
1690  // the device can allocate managed memory on this system
1691  value |= PI_USM_ACCESS;
1692  }
1693  if (getAttribute(device, CU_DEVICE_ATTRIBUTE_CONCURRENT_MANAGED_ACCESS)) {
1694  // all devices with the CU_DEVICE_ATTRIBUTE_CONCURRENT_MANAGED_ACCESS
1695  // attribute can coherently access managed memory concurrently with the
1696  // CPU
1697  value |= PI_USM_CONCURRENT_ACCESS;
1698  }
1699  if (getAttribute(device, CU_DEVICE_ATTRIBUTE_COMPUTE_CAPABILITY_MAJOR) >=
1700  6) {
1701  // compute capability 6.x introduces operations that are atomic with
1702  // respect to other CPUs and GPUs in the system
1703  if (value & PI_USM_ACCESS)
1704  value |= PI_USM_ATOMIC_ACCESS;
1705  if (value & PI_USM_CONCURRENT_ACCESS)
1706  value |= PI_USM_CONCURRENT_ATOMIC_ACCESS;
1707  }
1708  return getInfo(param_value_size, param_value, param_value_size_ret, value);
1709  }
1710  case PI_DEVICE_INFO_USM_SYSTEM_SHARED_SUPPORT: {
1711  // from cl_intel_unified_shared_memory:
1712  // "The shared system memory access capabilities apply to any allocations
1713  // made by a system allocator, such as malloc or new."
1714  //
1715  // query if/how the device can access pageable host memory allocated by the
1716  // system allocator
1717  pi_bitfield value = {};
1718  if (getAttribute(device, CU_DEVICE_ATTRIBUTE_PAGEABLE_MEMORY_ACCESS)) {
1719  // the device suppports coherently accessing pageable memory without
1720  // calling cuMemHostRegister/cudaHostRegister on it
1721  if (getAttribute(device,
1722  CU_DEVICE_ATTRIBUTE_HOST_NATIVE_ATOMIC_SUPPORTED)) {
1723  // the link between the device and the host supports native atomic
1724  // operations
1725  value = PI_USM_ACCESS | PI_USM_ATOMIC_ACCESS |
1726  PI_USM_CONCURRENT_ACCESS | PI_USM_CONCURRENT_ATOMIC_ACCESS;
1727  } else {
1728  // the link between the device and the host does not support native
1729  // atomic operations
1730  value = PI_USM_ACCESS | PI_USM_CONCURRENT_ACCESS;
1731  }
1732  }
1733  return getInfo(param_value_size, param_value, param_value_size_ret, value);
1734  }

1815 pi_result cuda_piContextCreate(const pi_context_properties *properties,
1816  pi_uint32 num_devices, const pi_device *devices,
1817  void (*pfn_notify)(const char *errinfo,
1818  const void *private_info,
1819  size_t cb, void *user_data),
1820  void *user_data, pi_context *retcontext) {
1821 
1822  assert(devices != nullptr);
1823  // TODO: How to implement context callback?
1824  assert(pfn_notify == nullptr);
1825  assert(user_data == nullptr);
1826  assert(num_devices == 1);
1827  // Need input context
1828  assert(retcontext != nullptr);
1829  pi_result errcode_ret = PI_SUCCESS;
1830 
1831  // Parse properties.
1832  bool property_cuda_primary = false;
1833  while (properties && (0 != *properties)) {
1834  // Consume property ID.
1835  pi_context_properties id = *properties;
1836  ++properties;
1837  // Consume property value.
1838  pi_context_properties value = *properties;
1839  ++properties;
1840  switch (id) {
1841  case __SYCL_PI_CONTEXT_PROPERTIES_CUDA_PRIMARY:
1842  assert(value == PI_FALSE || value == PI_TRUE);
1843  property_cuda_primary = static_cast<bool>(value);
1844  break;
1845  default:
1846  // Unknown property.
1847  cl::sycl::detail::pi::die(
1848  "Unknown piContextCreate property in property list");
1849  return PI_INVALID_VALUE;
1850  }
1851  }
1852 
1853  std::unique_ptr<_pi_context> piContextPtr{nullptr};
1854  try {
1855  CUcontext current = nullptr;
1856 
1857  if (property_cuda_primary) {
1858  // Use the CUDA primary context and assume that we want to use it
1859  // immediately as we want to forge context switches.
1860  CUcontext Ctxt;
1861  errcode_ret =
1862  PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuDevicePrimaryCtxRetain(&Ctxt, devices[0]->get()));
1863  piContextPtr = std::unique_ptr<_pi_context>(
1864  new _pi_context{_pi_context::kind::primary, Ctxt, *devices});
1865  errcode_ret = PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuCtxPushCurrent(Ctxt));
1866  } else {
1867  // Create a scoped context.
1868  CUcontext newContext;
1869  PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuCtxGetCurrent(&current));
1870  errcode_ret = PI_CHECK_ERROR(
1871  cuCtxCreate(&newContext, CU_CTX_MAP_HOST, devices[0]->get()));
1872  piContextPtr = std::unique_ptr<_pi_context>(new _pi_context{
1873  _pi_context::kind::user_defined, newContext, *devices});
1874  }
1875 
1876  // Use default stream to record base event counter
1877  PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuEventCreate(&piContextPtr->evBase_, CU_EVENT_DEFAULT));
1878  PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuEventRecord(piContextPtr->evBase_, 0));
1879 
1880  // For non-primary scoped contexts keep the last active on top of the stack
1881  // as `cuCtxCreate` replaces it implicitly otherwise.
1882  // Primary contexts are kept on top of the stack, so the previous context
1883  // is not queried and therefore not recovered.
1884  if (current != nullptr) {
1885  PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuCtxSetCurrent(current));
1886  }
1887 
1888  *retcontext = piContextPtr.release();
1889  } catch (pi_result err) {
1890  errcode_ret = err;
1891  } catch (...) {
1892  errcode_ret = PI_OUT_OF_RESOURCES;
1893  }
1894  return errcode_ret;
1895 }
1896 
1897 pi_result cuda_piContextRelease(pi_context ctxt) {
1898 
1899  assert(ctxt != nullptr);
1900 
1901  if (ctxt->decrement_reference_count() > 0) {
1902  return PI_SUCCESS;
1903  }
1904  ctxt->invoke_extended_deleters();
1905 
1906  std::unique_ptr<_pi_context> context{ctxt};
1907 
1908  PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuEventDestroy(context->evBase_));
1909 
1910  if (!ctxt->is_primary()) {
1911  CUcontext cuCtxt = ctxt->get();
1912  CUcontext current = nullptr;
1913  cuCtxGetCurrent(&current);
1914  if (cuCtxt != current) {
1915  PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuCtxPushCurrent(cuCtxt));
1916  }
1917  PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuCtxSynchronize());
1918  cuCtxGetCurrent(&current);
1919  if (cuCtxt == current) {
1920  PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuCtxPopCurrent(&current));
1921  }
1922  return PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuCtxDestroy(cuCtxt));
1923  } else {
1924  // Primary context is not destroyed, but released
1925  CUdevice cuDev = ctxt->get_device()->get();
1926  CUcontext current;
1927  cuCtxPopCurrent(&current);
1928  return PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuDevicePrimaryCtxRelease(cuDev));
1929  }
1930 }

1964 pi_result cuda_piMemBufferCreate(pi_context context, pi_mem_flags flags,
1965  size_t size, void *host_ptr, pi_mem *ret_mem,
1966  const pi_mem_properties *properties) {
1967  // Need input memory object
1968  assert(ret_mem != nullptr);
1969  assert(properties == nullptr && "no mem properties goes to cuda RT yet");
1970  // Currently, USE_HOST_PTR is not implemented using host register
1971  // since this triggers a weird segfault after program ends.
1972  // Setting this constant to true enables testing that behavior.
1973  const bool enableUseHostPtr = false;
1974  const bool performInitialCopy =
1975  (flags & PI_MEM_FLAGS_HOST_PTR_COPY) ||
1976  ((flags & PI_MEM_FLAGS_HOST_PTR_USE) && !enableUseHostPtr);
1977  pi_result retErr = PI_SUCCESS;
1978  pi_mem retMemObj = nullptr;
1979 
1980  try {
1981  ScopedContext active(context);
1982  CUdeviceptr ptr;
1983  _pi_mem::mem_::buffer_mem_::alloc_mode allocMode =
1984  _pi_mem::mem_::buffer_mem_::alloc_mode::classic;
1985 
1986  if ((flags & PI_MEM_FLAGS_HOST_PTR_USE) && enableUseHostPtr) {
1987  retErr = PI_CHECK_ERROR(
1988  cuMemHostRegister(host_ptr, size, CU_MEMHOSTREGISTER_DEVICEMAP));
1989  retErr = PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuMemHostGetDevicePointer(&ptr, host_ptr, 0));
1990  allocMode = _pi_mem::mem_::buffer_mem_::alloc_mode::use_host_ptr;
1991  } else if (flags & PI_MEM_FLAGS_HOST_PTR_ALLOC) {
1992  retErr = PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuMemAllocHost(&host_ptr, size));
1993  retErr = PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuMemHostGetDevicePointer(&ptr, host_ptr, 0));
1994  allocMode = _pi_mem::mem_::buffer_mem_::alloc_mode::alloc_host_ptr;
1995  } else {
1996  retErr = PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuMemAlloc(&ptr, size));
1997  if (flags & PI_MEM_FLAGS_HOST_PTR_COPY) {
1998  allocMode = _pi_mem::mem_::buffer_mem_::alloc_mode::copy_in;
1999  }
2000  }
2001 
2002  if (retErr == PI_SUCCESS) {
2003  pi_mem parentBuffer = nullptr;
2004 
2005  auto piMemObj = std::unique_ptr<_pi_mem>(
2006  new _pi_mem{context, parentBuffer, allocMode, ptr, host_ptr, size});
2007  if (piMemObj != nullptr) {
2008  retMemObj = piMemObj.release();
2009  if (performInitialCopy) {
2010  // Operates on the default stream of the current CUDA context.
2011  retErr = PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuMemcpyHtoD(ptr, host_ptr, size));
2012  // Synchronize with default stream implicitly used by cuMemcpyHtoD
2013  // to make buffer data available on device before any other PI call
2014  // uses it.
2015  if (retErr == PI_SUCCESS) {
2016  CUstream defaultStream = 0;
2017  retErr = PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuStreamSynchronize(defaultStream));
2018  }
2019  }
2020  } else {
2021  retErr = PI_OUT_OF_HOST_MEMORY;
2022  }
2023  }
2024  } catch (pi_result err) {
2025  retErr = err;
2026  } catch (...) {
2027  retErr = PI_OUT_OF_RESOURCES;
2028  }
2029 
2030  *ret_mem = retMemObj;
2031 
2032  return retErr;
2033 }

2039 pi_result cuda_piMemRelease(pi_mem memObj) {
2040  assert((memObj != nullptr) && "PI_INVALID_MEM_OBJECTS");
2041 
2042  pi_result ret = PI_SUCCESS;
2043 
2044  try {
2045 
2046  // Do nothing if there are other references
2047  if (memObj->decrement_reference_count() > 0) {
2048  return PI_SUCCESS;
2049  }
2050 
2051  // make sure memObj is released in case PI_CHECK_ERROR throws
2052  std::unique_ptr<_pi_mem> uniqueMemObj(memObj);
2053 
2054  if (memObj->is_sub_buffer()) {
2055  return PI_SUCCESS;
2056  }
2057 
2058  ScopedContext active(uniqueMemObj->get_context());
2059 
2060  if (memObj->mem_type_ == _pi_mem::mem_type::buffer) {
2061  switch (uniqueMemObj->mem_.buffer_mem_.allocMode_) {
2062  case _pi_mem::mem_::buffer_mem_::alloc_mode::copy_in:
2063  case _pi_mem::mem_::buffer_mem_::alloc_mode::classic:
2064  ret = PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuMemFree(uniqueMemObj->mem_.buffer_mem_.ptr_));
2065  break;
2066  case _pi_mem::mem_::buffer_mem_::alloc_mode::use_host_ptr:
2067  ret = PI_CHECK_ERROR(
2068  cuMemHostUnregister(uniqueMemObj->mem_.buffer_mem_.hostPtr_));
2069  break;
2070  case _pi_mem::mem_::buffer_mem_::alloc_mode::alloc_host_ptr:
2071  ret = PI_CHECK_ERROR(
2072  cuMemFreeHost(uniqueMemObj->mem_.buffer_mem_.hostPtr_));
2073  };
2074  } else if (memObj->mem_type_ == _pi_mem::mem_type::surface) {
2075  ret = PI_CHECK_ERROR(
2076  cuSurfObjectDestroy(uniqueMemObj->mem_.surface_mem_.get_surface()));
2077  ret = PI_CHECK_ERROR(
2078  cuArrayDestroy(uniqueMemObj->mem_.surface_mem_.get_array()));
2079  }
2080 
2081  } catch (pi_result err) {
2082  ret = err;
2083  } catch (...) {
2084  ret = PI_OUT_OF_RESOURCES;
2085  }
2086 
2087  if (ret != PI_SUCCESS) {
2088  // A reported CUDA error is either an implementation or an asynchronous CUDA
2089  // error for which it is unclear if the function that reported it succeeded
2090  // or not. Either way, the state of the program is compromised and likely
2091  // unrecoverable.
2092  cl::sycl::detail::pi::die(
2093  "Unrecoverable program state reached in cuda_piMemRelease");
2094  }
2095 
2096  return PI_SUCCESS;
2097 }

2463 pi_result cuda_piEventsWait(pi_uint32 num_events, const pi_event *event_list) {
2464 
2465  try {
2466  assert(num_events != 0);
2467  assert(event_list);
2468  if (num_events == 0) {
2469  return PI_INVALID_VALUE;
2470  }
2471 
2472  if (!event_list) {
2473  return PI_INVALID_EVENT;
2474  }
2475 
2476  auto context = event_list[0]->get_context();
2477  ScopedContext active(context);
2478 
2479  auto waitFunc = [context](pi_event event) -> pi_result {
2480  if (!event) {
2481  return PI_INVALID_EVENT;
2482  }
2483 
2484  if (event->get_context() != context) {
2485  return PI_INVALID_CONTEXT;
2486  }
2487 
2488  return event->wait();
2489  };
2490  return forLatestEvents(event_list, num_events, waitFunc);
2491  } catch (pi_result err) {
2492  return err;
2493  } catch (...) {
2494  return PI_OUT_OF_RESOURCES;
2495  }
2496 }

2604 pi_result cuda_piKernelGetGroupInfo(pi_kernel kernel, pi_device device,
2605  pi_kernel_group_info param_name,
2606  size_t param_value_size, void *param_value,
2607  size_t *param_value_size_ret) {
2608 
2609  // Here we want to query about a kernel's cuda blocks!
2610 
2611  if (kernel != nullptr) {
2612 
2613  switch (param_name) {
2614  case PI_KERNEL_GROUP_INFO_WORK_GROUP_SIZE: {
2615  int max_threads = 0;
2616  cl::sycl::detail::pi::assertion(
2617  cuFuncGetAttribute(&max_threads,
2618  CU_FUNC_ATTRIBUTE_MAX_THREADS_PER_BLOCK,
2619  kernel->get()) == CUDA_SUCCESS);
2620  return getInfo(param_value_size, param_value, param_value_size_ret,
2621  size_t(max_threads));
2622  }
2623  case PI_KERNEL_GROUP_INFO_COMPILE_WORK_GROUP_SIZE: {
2624  size_t group_size[3] = {0, 0, 0};
2625  const auto &reqd_wg_size_md_map =
2626  kernel->program_->kernelReqdWorkGroupSizeMD_;
2627  const auto reqd_wg_size_md = reqd_wg_size_md_map.find(kernel->name_);
2628  if (reqd_wg_size_md != reqd_wg_size_md_map.end()) {
2629  const auto reqd_wg_size = reqd_wg_size_md->second;
2630  group_size[0] = std::get<0>(reqd_wg_size);
2631  group_size[1] = std::get<1>(reqd_wg_size);
2632  group_size[2] = std::get<2>(reqd_wg_size);
2633  }
2634  return getInfoArray(3, param_value_size, param_value,
2635  param_value_size_ret, group_size);
2636  }
2637  case PI_KERNEL_GROUP_INFO_LOCAL_MEM_SIZE: {
2638  // OpenCL LOCAL == CUDA SHARED
2639  int bytes = 0;
2640  cl::sycl::detail::pi::assertion(
2641  cuFuncGetAttribute(&bytes, CU_FUNC_ATTRIBUTE_SHARED_SIZE_BYTES,
2642  kernel->get()) == CUDA_SUCCESS);
2643  return getInfo(param_value_size, param_value, param_value_size_ret,
2644  pi_uint64(bytes));
2645  }
2646  case PI_KERNEL_GROUP_INFO_PREFERRED_WORK_GROUP_SIZE_MULTIPLE: {
2647  // Work groups should be multiples of the warp size
2648  int warpSize = 0;
2649  cl::sycl::detail::pi::assertion(
2650  cuDeviceGetAttribute(&warpSize, CU_DEVICE_ATTRIBUTE_WARP_SIZE,
2651  device->get()) == CUDA_SUCCESS);
2652  return getInfo(param_value_size, param_value, param_value_size_ret,
2653  static_cast<size_t>(warpSize));
2654  }
2655  case PI_KERNEL_GROUP_INFO_PRIVATE_MEM_SIZE: {
2656  // OpenCL PRIVATE == CUDA LOCAL
2657  int bytes = 0;
2658  cl::sycl::detail::pi::assertion(
2659  cuFuncGetAttribute(&bytes, CU_FUNC_ATTRIBUTE_LOCAL_SIZE_BYTES,
2660  kernel->get()) == CUDA_SUCCESS);
2661  return getInfo(param_value_size, param_value, param_value_size_ret,
2662  pi_uint64(bytes));
2663  }
2664  case PI_KERNEL_GROUP_INFO_NUM_REGS: {
2665  int numRegs = 0;
2666  cl::sycl::detail::pi::assertion(
2667  cuFuncGetAttribute(&numRegs, CU_FUNC_ATTRIBUTE_NUM_REGS,
2668  kernel->get()) == CUDA_SUCCESS);
2669  return getInfo(param_value_size, param_value, param_value_size_ret,
2670  pi_uint32(numRegs));
2671  }
2672  default:
2673  __SYCL_PI_HANDLE_UNKNOWN_PARAM_NAME(param_name);
2674  }
2675  }
2676 
2677  return PI_INVALID_KERNEL;
2678 }

2680 pi_result cuda_piEnqueueKernelLaunch(
2681  pi_queue command_queue, pi_kernel kernel, pi_uint32 work_dim,
2682  const size_t *global_work_offset, const size_t *global_work_size,
2683  const size_t *local_work_size, pi_uint32 num_events_in_wait_list,
2684  const pi_event *event_wait_list, pi_event *event) {
2685 
2686  // Preconditions
2687  assert(command_queue != nullptr);
2688  assert(command_queue->get_context() == kernel->get_context());
2689  assert(kernel != nullptr);
2690  assert(global_work_offset != nullptr);
2691  assert(work_dim > 0);
2692  assert(work_dim < 4);
2693 
2694  // Set the number of threads per block to the number of threads per warp
2695  // by default unless user has provided a better number
2696  size_t threadsPerBlock[3] = {32u, 1u, 1u};
2697  size_t maxWorkGroupSize = 0u;
2698  size_t maxThreadsPerBlock[3] = {};
2699  bool providedLocalWorkGroupSize = (local_work_size != nullptr);
2700  pi_uint32 local_size = kernel->get_local_size();
2701  pi_result retError = PI_SUCCESS;
2702 
2703  try {
2704  // Set the active context here as guessLocalWorkSize needs an active context
2705  ScopedContext active(command_queue->get_context());
2706  {
2707  size_t *reqdThreadsPerBlock = kernel->reqdThreadsPerBlock_;
2708  maxWorkGroupSize = command_queue->device_->get_max_work_group_size();
2709  command_queue->device_->get_max_work_item_sizes(
2710  sizeof(maxThreadsPerBlock), maxThreadsPerBlock);
2711 
2712  if (providedLocalWorkGroupSize) {
2713  auto isValid = [&](int dim) {
2714  if (reqdThreadsPerBlock[dim] != 0 &&
2715  local_work_size[dim] != reqdThreadsPerBlock[dim])
2716  return PI_INVALID_WORK_GROUP_SIZE;
2717 
2718  if (local_work_size[dim] > maxThreadsPerBlock[dim])
2719  return PI_INVALID_WORK_ITEM_SIZE;
2720  // Checks that local work sizes are a divisor of the global work sizes
2721  // which includes that the local work sizes are neither larger than
2722  // the global work sizes and not 0.
2723  if (0u == local_work_size[dim])
2724  return PI_INVALID_WORK_GROUP_SIZE;
2725  if (0u != (global_work_size[dim] % local_work_size[dim]))
2726  return PI_INVALID_WORK_GROUP_SIZE;
2727  threadsPerBlock[dim] = local_work_size[dim];
2728  return PI_SUCCESS;
2729  };
2730 
2731  for (size_t dim = 0; dim < work_dim; dim++) {
2732  auto err = isValid(dim);
2733  if (err != PI_SUCCESS)
2734  return err;
2735  }
2736  } else {
2737  guessLocalWorkSize(threadsPerBlock, global_work_size,
2738  maxThreadsPerBlock, kernel, local_size);
2739  }
2740  }
2741 
2742  if (maxWorkGroupSize <
2743  size_t(threadsPerBlock[0] * threadsPerBlock[1] * threadsPerBlock[2])) {
2744  return PI_INVALID_WORK_GROUP_SIZE;
2745  }
2746 
2747  size_t blocksPerGrid[3] = {1u, 1u, 1u};
2748 
2749  for (size_t i = 0; i < work_dim; i++) {
2750  blocksPerGrid[i] =
2751  (global_work_size[i] + threadsPerBlock[i] - 1) / threadsPerBlock[i];
2752  }
2753 
2754  std::unique_ptr<_pi_event> retImplEv{nullptr};
2755 
2756  CUstream cuStream = command_queue->get();
2757  CUfunction cuFunc = kernel->get();
2758 
2759  if (event_wait_list) {
2760  retError = cuda_piEnqueueEventsWait(
2761  command_queue, num_events_in_wait_list, event_wait_list, nullptr);
2762  }
2763 
2764  // Set the implicit global offset parameter if kernel has offset variant
2765  if (kernel->get_with_offset_parameter()) {
2766  std::uint32_t cuda_implicit_offset[3] = {0, 0, 0};
2767  if (global_work_offset) {
2768  for (size_t i = 0; i < work_dim; i++) {
2769  cuda_implicit_offset[i] =
2770  static_cast<std::uint32_t>(global_work_offset[i]);
2771  if (global_work_offset[i] != 0) {
2772  cuFunc = kernel->get_with_offset_parameter();
2773  }
2774  }
2775  }
2776  kernel->set_implicit_offset_arg(sizeof(cuda_implicit_offset),
2777  cuda_implicit_offset);
2778  }
2779 
2780  auto &argIndices = kernel->get_arg_indices();
2781 
2782  if (event) {
2783  retImplEv = std::unique_ptr<_pi_event>(_pi_event::make_native(
2784  PI_COMMAND_TYPE_NDRANGE_KERNEL, command_queue));
2785  retImplEv->start();
2786  }
2787 
2788  retError = PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuLaunchKernel(
2789  cuFunc, blocksPerGrid[0], blocksPerGrid[1], blocksPerGrid[2],
2790  threadsPerBlock[0], threadsPerBlock[1], threadsPerBlock[2], local_size,
2791  cuStream, const_cast<void **>(argIndices.data()), nullptr));
2792  if (local_size != 0)
2793  kernel->clear_local_size();
2794 
2795  if (event) {
2796  retError = retImplEv->record();
2797  *event = retImplEv.release();
2798  }
2799  } catch (pi_result err) {
2800  retError = err;
2801  }
2802  return retError;
2803 }

2821 pi_result cuda_piMemImageCreate(pi_context context, pi_mem_flags flags,
2822  const pi_image_format *image_format,
2823  const pi_image_desc *image_desc, void *host_ptr,
2824  pi_mem *ret_mem) {
2825  // Need input memory object
2826  assert(ret_mem != nullptr);
2827  const bool performInitialCopy = (flags & PI_MEM_FLAGS_HOST_PTR_COPY) ||
2828  ((flags & PI_MEM_FLAGS_HOST_PTR_USE));
2829  pi_result retErr = PI_SUCCESS;
2830 
2831  // We only support RBGA channel order
2832  // TODO: check SYCL CTS and spec. May also have to support BGRA
2833  if (image_format->image_channel_order !=
2834  pi_image_channel_order::PI_IMAGE_CHANNEL_ORDER_RGBA) {
2835  cl::sycl::detail::pi::die(
2836  "cuda_piMemImageCreate only supports RGBA channel order");
2837  }
2838 
2839  // We have to use cuArray3DCreate, which has some caveats. The height and
2840  // depth parameters must be set to 0 produce 1D or 2D arrays. image_desc gives
2841  // a minimum value of 1, so we need to convert the answer.
2842  CUDA_ARRAY3D_DESCRIPTOR array_desc;
2843  array_desc.NumChannels = 4; // Only support 4 channel image
2844  array_desc.Flags = 0; // No flags required
2845  array_desc.Width = image_desc->image_width;
2846  if (image_desc->image_type == PI_MEM_TYPE_IMAGE1D) {
2847  array_desc.Height = 0;
2848  array_desc.Depth = 0;
2849  } else if (image_desc->image_type == PI_MEM_TYPE_IMAGE2D) {
2850  array_desc.Height = image_desc->image_height;
2851  array_desc.Depth = 0;
2852  } else if (image_desc->image_type == PI_MEM_TYPE_IMAGE3D) {
2853  array_desc.Height = image_desc->image_height;
2854  array_desc.Depth = image_desc->image_depth;
2855  }
2856 
2857  // We need to get this now in bytes for calculating the total image size later
2858  size_t pixel_type_size_bytes;
2859 
2860  switch (image_format->image_channel_data_type) {
2861  case PI_IMAGE_CHANNEL_TYPE_UNORM_INT8:
2862  case PI_IMAGE_CHANNEL_TYPE_UNSIGNED_INT8:
2863  array_desc.Format = CU_AD_FORMAT_UNSIGNED_INT8;
2864  pixel_type_size_bytes = 1;
2865  break;
2866  case PI_IMAGE_CHANNEL_TYPE_SIGNED_INT8:
2867  array_desc.Format = CU_AD_FORMAT_SIGNED_INT8;
2868  pixel_type_size_bytes = 1;
2869  break;
2870  case PI_IMAGE_CHANNEL_TYPE_UNORM_INT16:
2871  case PI_IMAGE_CHANNEL_TYPE_UNSIGNED_INT16:
2872  array_desc.Format = CU_AD_FORMAT_UNSIGNED_INT16;
2873  pixel_type_size_bytes = 2;
2874  break;
2875  case PI_IMAGE_CHANNEL_TYPE_SIGNED_INT16:
2876  array_desc.Format = CU_AD_FORMAT_SIGNED_INT16;
2877  pixel_type_size_bytes = 2;
2878  break;
2879  case PI_IMAGE_CHANNEL_TYPE_HALF_FLOAT:
2880  array_desc.Format = CU_AD_FORMAT_HALF;
2881  pixel_type_size_bytes = 2;
2882  break;
2883  case PI_IMAGE_CHANNEL_TYPE_UNSIGNED_INT32:
2884  array_desc.Format = CU_AD_FORMAT_UNSIGNED_INT32;
2885  pixel_type_size_bytes = 4;
2886  break;
2887  case PI_IMAGE_CHANNEL_TYPE_SIGNED_INT32:
2888  array_desc.Format = CU_AD_FORMAT_SIGNED_INT32;
2889  pixel_type_size_bytes = 4;
2890  break;
2891  case PI_IMAGE_CHANNEL_TYPE_FLOAT:
2892  array_desc.Format = CU_AD_FORMAT_FLOAT;
2893  pixel_type_size_bytes = 4;
2894  break;
2895  default:
2896  cl::sycl::detail::pi::die(
2897  "cuda_piMemImageCreate given unsupported image_channel_data_type");
2898  }
2899 
2900  // When a dimension isn't used image_desc has the size set to 1
2901  size_t pixel_size_bytes =
2902  pixel_type_size_bytes * 4; // 4 is the only number of channels we support
2903  size_t image_size_bytes = pixel_size_bytes * image_desc->image_width *
2904  image_desc->image_height * image_desc->image_depth;
2905 
2906  ScopedContext active(context);
2907  CUarray image_array;
2908  retErr = PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuArray3DCreate(&image_array, &array_desc));
2909 
2910  try {
2911  if (performInitialCopy) {
2912  // We have to use a different copy function for each image dimensionality
2913  if (image_desc->image_type == PI_MEM_TYPE_IMAGE1D) {
2914  retErr = PI_CHECK_ERROR(
2915  cuMemcpyHtoA(image_array, 0, host_ptr, image_size_bytes));
2916  } else if (image_desc->image_type == PI_MEM_TYPE_IMAGE2D) {
2917  CUDA_MEMCPY2D cpy_desc;
2918  memset(&cpy_desc, 0, sizeof(cpy_desc));
2919  cpy_desc.srcMemoryType = CUmemorytype_enum::CU_MEMORYTYPE_HOST;
2920  cpy_desc.srcHost = host_ptr;
2921  cpy_desc.dstMemoryType = CUmemorytype_enum::CU_MEMORYTYPE_ARRAY;
2922  cpy_desc.dstArray = image_array;
2923  cpy_desc.WidthInBytes = pixel_size_bytes * image_desc->image_width;
2924  cpy_desc.Height = image_desc->image_height;
2925  retErr = PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuMemcpy2D(&cpy_desc));
2926  } else if (image_desc->image_type == PI_MEM_TYPE_IMAGE3D) {
2927  CUDA_MEMCPY3D cpy_desc;
2928  memset(&cpy_desc, 0, sizeof(cpy_desc));
2929  cpy_desc.srcMemoryType = CUmemorytype_enum::CU_MEMORYTYPE_HOST;
2930  cpy_desc.srcHost = host_ptr;
2931  cpy_desc.dstMemoryType = CUmemorytype_enum::CU_MEMORYTYPE_ARRAY;
2932  cpy_desc.dstArray = image_array;
2933  cpy_desc.WidthInBytes = pixel_size_bytes * image_desc->image_width;
2934  cpy_desc.Height = image_desc->image_height;
2935  cpy_desc.Depth = image_desc->image_depth;
2936  retErr = PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuMemcpy3D(&cpy_desc));
2937  }
2938  }
2939 
2940  // CUDA_RESOURCE_DESC is a union of different structs, shown here
2941  // https://docs.nvidia.com/cuda/cuda-driver-api/group__CUDA__TEXOBJECT.html
2942  // We need to fill it as described here to use it for a surface or texture
2943  // https://docs.nvidia.com/cuda/cuda-driver-api/group__CUDA__SURFOBJECT.html
2944  // CUDA_RESOURCE_DESC::resType must be CU_RESOURCE_TYPE_ARRAY and
2945  // CUDA_RESOURCE_DESC::res::array::hArray must be set to a valid CUDA array
2946  // handle.
2947  // CUDA_RESOURCE_DESC::flags must be set to zero
2948 
2949  CUDA_RESOURCE_DESC image_res_desc;
2950  image_res_desc.res.array.hArray = image_array;
2951  image_res_desc.resType = CU_RESOURCE_TYPE_ARRAY;
2952  image_res_desc.flags = 0;
2953 
2954  CUsurfObject surface;
2955  retErr = PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuSurfObjectCreate(&surface, &image_res_desc));
2956 
2957  auto piMemObj = std::unique_ptr<_pi_mem>(new _pi_mem{
2958  context, image_array, surface, image_desc->image_type, host_ptr});
2959 
2960  if (piMemObj == nullptr) {
2961  return PI_OUT_OF_HOST_MEMORY;
2962  }
2963 
2964  *ret_mem = piMemObj.release();
2965  } catch (pi_result err) {
2966  cuArrayDestroy(image_array);
2967  return err;
2968  } catch (...) {
2969  cuArrayDestroy(image_array);
2970  return PI_ERROR_UNKNOWN;
2971  }
2972 
2973  return retErr;
2974 }

3118 pi_result cuda_piProgramLink(pi_context context, pi_uint32 num_devices,
3119  const pi_device *device_list, const char *options,
3120  pi_uint32 num_input_programs,
3121  const pi_program *input_programs,
3122  void (*pfn_notify)(pi_program program,
3123  void *user_data),
3124  void *user_data, pi_program *ret_program) {
3125 
3126  assert(ret_program != nullptr);
3127  assert(num_devices == 1 || num_devices == 0);
3128  assert(device_list != nullptr || num_devices == 0);
3129  assert(pfn_notify == nullptr);
3130  assert(user_data == nullptr);
3131  pi_result retError = PI_SUCCESS;
3132 
3133  try {
3134  ScopedContext active(context);
3135 
3136  CUlinkState state;
3137  std::unique_ptr<_pi_program> retProgram{new _pi_program{context}};
3138 
3139  retError = PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuLinkCreate(0, nullptr, nullptr, &state));
3140  try {
3141  for (size_t i = 0; i < num_input_programs; ++i) {
3142  pi_program program = input_programs[i];
3143  retError = PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuLinkAddData(
3144  state, CU_JIT_INPUT_PTX, const_cast<char *>(program->binary_),
3145  program->binarySizeInBytes_, nullptr, 0, nullptr, nullptr));
3146  }
3147  void *cubin = nullptr;
3148  size_t cubinSize = 0;
3149  retError = PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuLinkComplete(state, &cubin, &cubinSize));
3150 
3151  retError =
3152  retProgram->set_binary(static_cast<const char *>(cubin), cubinSize);
3153 
3154  if (retError != PI_SUCCESS) {
3155  return retError;
3156  }
3157 
3158  retError = retProgram->build_program(options);
3159 
3160  if (retError != PI_SUCCESS) {
3161  return retError;
3162  }
3163  } catch (...) {
3164  // Upon error attempt cleanup
3165  PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuLinkDestroy(state));
3166  throw;
3167  }
3168 
3169  retError = PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuLinkDestroy(state));
3170  *ret_program = retProgram.release();
3171 
3172  } catch (pi_result err) {
3173  retError = err;
3174  }
3175  return retError;

3645 pi_result cuda_piSamplerCreate(pi_context context,
3646  const pi_sampler_properties *sampler_properties,
3647  pi_sampler *result_sampler) {
3648  std::unique_ptr<_pi_sampler> retImplSampl{new _pi_sampler(context)};
3649 
3650  bool propSeen[3] = {false, false, false};
3651  for (size_t i = 0; sampler_properties[i] != 0; i += 2) {
3652  switch (sampler_properties[i]) {
3653  case PI_SAMPLER_PROPERTIES_NORMALIZED_COORDS:
3654  if (propSeen[0]) {
3655  return PI_INVALID_VALUE;
3656  }
3657  propSeen[0] = true;
3658  retImplSampl->props_ |= sampler_properties[i + 1];
3659  break;
3660  case PI_SAMPLER_PROPERTIES_FILTER_MODE:
3661  if (propSeen[1]) {
3662  return PI_INVALID_VALUE;
3663  }
3664  propSeen[1] = true;
3665  retImplSampl->props_ |=
3666  (sampler_properties[i + 1] - PI_SAMPLER_FILTER_MODE_NEAREST) << 1;
3667  break;
3668  case PI_SAMPLER_PROPERTIES_ADDRESSING_MODE:
3669  if (propSeen[2]) {
3670  return PI_INVALID_VALUE;
3671  }
3672  propSeen[2] = true;
3673  retImplSampl->props_ |=
3674  (sampler_properties[i + 1] - PI_SAMPLER_ADDRESSING_MODE_NONE) << 2;
3675  break;
3676  default:
3677  return PI_INVALID_VALUE;
3678  }
3679  }
3680 
3681  if (!propSeen[0]) {
3682  retImplSampl->props_ |= CL_TRUE;
3683  }
3684  // Default filter mode to CL_FILTER_NEAREST
3685  if (!propSeen[2]) {
3686  retImplSampl->props_ |= (CL_ADDRESS_CLAMP % CL_ADDRESS_NONE) << 2;
3687  }
3688 
3689  *result_sampler = retImplSampl.release();
3690  return PI_SUCCESS;
3691 }

4030 pi_result cuda_piEnqueueMemBufferFill(pi_queue command_queue, pi_mem buffer,
4031  const void *pattern, size_t pattern_size,
4032  size_t offset, size_t size,
4033  pi_uint32 num_events_in_wait_list,
4034  const pi_event *event_wait_list,
4035  pi_event *event) {
4036  assert(command_queue != nullptr);
4037 
4038  auto args_are_multiples_of_pattern_size =
4039  (offset % pattern_size == 0) || (size % pattern_size == 0);
4040 
4041  auto pattern_is_valid = (pattern != nullptr);
4042 
4043  auto pattern_size_is_valid =
4044  ((pattern_size & (pattern_size - 1)) == 0) && // is power of two
4045  (pattern_size > 0) && (pattern_size <= 128); // falls within valid range
4046 
4047  assert(args_are_multiples_of_pattern_size && pattern_is_valid &&
4048  pattern_size_is_valid);
4049  (void)args_are_multiples_of_pattern_size;
4050  (void)pattern_is_valid;
4051  (void)pattern_size_is_valid;
4052 
4053  std::unique_ptr<_pi_event> retImplEv{nullptr};
4054 
4055  try {
4056  ScopedContext active(command_queue->get_context());
4057 
4058  if (event_wait_list) {
4059  cuda_piEnqueueEventsWait(command_queue, num_events_in_wait_list,
4060  event_wait_list, nullptr);
4061  }
4062 
4063  pi_result result;
4064 
4065  if (event) {
4066  retImplEv = std::unique_ptr<_pi_event>(_pi_event::make_native(
4067  PI_COMMAND_TYPE_MEM_BUFFER_FILL, command_queue));
4068  result = retImplEv->start();
4069  }
4070 
4071  auto dstDevice = buffer->mem_.buffer_mem_.get() + offset;
4072  auto stream = command_queue->get();
4073  auto N = size / pattern_size;
4074 
4075  // pattern size in bytes
4076  switch (pattern_size) {
4077  case 1: {
4078  auto value = *static_cast<const uint8_t *>(pattern);
4079  result = PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuMemsetD8Async(dstDevice, value, N, stream));
4080  break;
4081  }
4082  case 2: {
4083  auto value = *static_cast<const uint16_t *>(pattern);
4084  result = PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuMemsetD16Async(dstDevice, value, N, stream));
4085  break;
4086  }
4087  case 4: {
4088  auto value = *static_cast<const uint32_t *>(pattern);
4089  result = PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuMemsetD32Async(dstDevice, value, N, stream));
4090  break;
4091  }
4092  default: {
4093  // CUDA has no memset functions that allow setting values more than 4
4094  // bytes. PI API lets you pass an arbitrary "pattern" to the buffer
4095  // fill, which can be more than 4 bytes. We must break up the pattern
4096  // into 4 byte values, and set the buffer using multiple strided calls.
4097  // This means that one cuMemsetD2D32Async call is made for every 4 bytes
4098  // in the pattern.
4099 
4100  auto number_of_steps = pattern_size / sizeof(uint32_t);
4101 
4102  // we walk up the pattern in 4-byte steps, and call cuMemset for each
4103  // 4-byte chunk of the pattern.
4104  for (auto step = 0u; step < number_of_steps; ++step) {
4105  // take 4 bytes of the pattern
4106  auto value = *(static_cast<const uint32_t *>(pattern) + step);
4107 
4108  // offset the pointer to the part of the buffer we want to write to
4109  auto offset_ptr = dstDevice + (step * sizeof(uint32_t));
4110 
4111  // set all of the pattern chunks
4112  result = PI_CHECK_ERROR(
4113  cuMemsetD2D32Async(offset_ptr, pattern_size, value, 1, N, stream));
4114  }
4115 
4116  break;
4117  }
4118  }
4119 
4120  if (event) {
4121  result = retImplEv->record();
4122  *event = retImplEv.release();
4123  }
4124 
4125  return result;
4126  } catch (pi_result err) {
4127  return err;
4128  } catch (...) {
4129  return PI_ERROR_UNKNOWN;
4130  }
4131 }

4133 static size_t imageElementByteSize(CUDA_ARRAY_DESCRIPTOR array_desc) {
4134  switch (array_desc.Format) {
4135  case CU_AD_FORMAT_UNSIGNED_INT8:
4136  case CU_AD_FORMAT_SIGNED_INT8:
4137  return 1;
4138  case CU_AD_FORMAT_UNSIGNED_INT16:
4139  case CU_AD_FORMAT_SIGNED_INT16:
4140  case CU_AD_FORMAT_HALF:
4141  return 2;
4142  case CU_AD_FORMAT_UNSIGNED_INT32:
4143  case CU_AD_FORMAT_SIGNED_INT32:
4144  case CU_AD_FORMAT_FLOAT:
4145  return 4;
4146  default:
4147  cl::sycl::detail::pi::die("Invalid image format.");
4148  return 0;
4149  }
4150 }

4848 pi_result cuda_piextUSMGetMemAllocInfo(pi_context context, const void *ptr,
4849  pi_mem_info param_name,
4850  size_t param_value_size,
4851  void *param_value,
4852  size_t *param_value_size_ret) {
4853  assert(context != nullptr);
4854  assert(ptr != nullptr);
4855  pi_result result = PI_SUCCESS;
4856 
4857  try {
4858  ScopedContext active(context);
4859  switch (param_name) {
4860  case PI_MEM_ALLOC_TYPE: {
4861  unsigned int value;
4862  // do not throw if cuPointerGetAttribute returns CUDA_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE
4863  CUresult ret = cuPointerGetAttribute(
4864  &value, CU_POINTER_ATTRIBUTE_IS_MANAGED, (CUdeviceptr)ptr);
4865  if (ret == CUDA_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE) {
4866  // pointer not known to the CUDA subsystem
4867  return getInfo(param_value_size, param_value, param_value_size_ret,
4868  PI_MEM_TYPE_UNKNOWN);
4869  }
4870  result = check_error(ret, __func__, __LINE__ - 5, __FILE__);
4871  if (value) {
4872  // pointer to managed memory
4873  return getInfo(param_value_size, param_value, param_value_size_ret,
4874  PI_MEM_TYPE_SHARED);
4875  }
4876  result = PI_CHECK_ERROR(cuPointerGetAttribute(
4877  &value, CU_POINTER_ATTRIBUTE_MEMORY_TYPE, (CUdeviceptr)ptr));
4878  assert(value == CU_MEMORYTYPE_DEVICE || value == CU_MEMORYTYPE_HOST);
4879  if (value == CU_MEMORYTYPE_DEVICE) {
4880  // pointer to device memory
4881  return getInfo(param_value_size, param_value, param_value_size_ret,
4882  PI_MEM_TYPE_DEVICE);
4883  }
4884  if (value == CU_MEMORYTYPE_HOST) {
4885  // pointer to host memory
4886  return getInfo(param_value_size, param_value, param_value_size_ret,
4887  PI_MEM_TYPE_HOST);
4888  }
4889  // should never get here
4890 #ifdef _MSC_VER
4891  __assume(0);
4892 #else
4893  __builtin_unreachable();
4894 #endif
4895  return getInfo(param_value_size, param_value, param_value_size_ret,
4896  PI_MEM_TYPE_UNKNOWN);
4897  }
4898  case PI_MEM_ALLOC_BASE_PTR: {
4899 #if __CUDA_API_VERSION >= 10020
4900  // CU_POINTER_ATTRIBUTE_RANGE_START_ADDR was introduced in CUDA 10.2
